A lot of people have been asking how I curl my hair so here it is!! 🫶🏽 

I personally use the Hot Tools 1” curling iron. (I’ve never been big on wands) but I love the look it gives and I feel like I save my fingers from getting burned 😂 also remember heat protectant is your friend so make sure you’re using some!!! 

Another 🔑 thing I’ve found for adding volume to my hair but not keeping the curls so harsh is shaking my hair upside down and side to side lol and scrunching up the curls but NEVER brushing or combing through.

One thing I’ve learned on this journey of motherhood is that everyone’s looks so different. 

I made a decision that I wasn’t going to listen to the people who think they know it all (especially the negative Nancy’s) and I was going to parent how I wanted to parent. 

It’s brought me so much peace and allowed me to enjoy this new chapter rather than be overwhelmed questioning everything. 

Just because someone does something one way doesn’t mean that’s the only way. You don’t like co sleeping? Cool then don’t do it. 

Don’t waste your time trying to tell me what I should and shouldn’t do with my child. 🫶🏽
life w/ you is my favorite 💙

Seeing their bond has been so special. I’m so lucky to be their mama 🥹

World Breastfeeding Week. 🌎✨

This journey hasn’t always been the easiest. As a matter of fact I almost stopped a week in because I was in so much pain.. I remember crying to Wesley about how I was thinking about stopping because I just couldn’t handle it. I was so heartbroken at the thought but I had someone tell me it gets better and I decided to push through. 

Here we are almost 7 months in and I’m on cloud 9. ☁️

It has been so special to have this bond and seeing him grow more and more each day. 

I wasn’t sure how feeding in public would be for me. I was nervous and scared but now I feel so empowered. I refuse to hide in my car or the bathroom. When my baby needs to eat he eats. Plain & simple. 

Every tear, every soaked bra, every rock hard boob because we slept through the night has been so worth it. 🤍

#worldbreastfeedingweek #momlife #babyboy #breastfeeding

Imposter Syndrome: 

When people doubt their own abilities and fear being exposed as frauds, despite all their accomplishments. 

It’s so wild that our minds try to play games and make us doubt ourselves and often times tries to stop so many of us from achieving the things we are meant for. 

Stop comparing yourself 
Stop doubting yourself 
Stop watering down your accomplishments 
Stop thinking you aren’t meant for big things 

You got this. Even when you feel like you don’t.. 

YOU DO. 

- Your Growth Guru 🌱

STOP getting stuck in the comparison game. Remember your path isn’t meant to look like anybody else’s. 

Your story is YOUR STORY. 

Can you imagine how boring life would be if we all were the exact same?

If you’re in a season of life where you feel like everyone around you is getting results and you aren’t. My advice is keep doing what you are doing, don’t get discouraged and know that your time is coming. 🗣️ 

Embrace your unique path, for its the only one that leads to genuine success. 

- Your Growth Guru 🌱

Sitting on our stairs in our first home that we built. UNREAL 

Here‘s to so many more memories 🤍🏡

GOD IS GREAT.

It’s so crazy to look back on our journey together over the last 2 years. 

When we first started dating we were renting a small bedroom together (Wesley had like 2 drawers for his stuff no joke 😂) 

Then when we found out I was pregnant we decided to get our own apartment together in San Diego. 

To moving to Texas and getting our 2nd apartment together. 

To now building &1 buying our first home. 🤍

So prepare to be sick of me because I am so excited and proud of us!!

I feel like these were all yesterday. 

My 24th surprise birthday party that Wesley & my friends threw, the day before I found out I was pregnant and our gender reveal. 🤍

The outfits might not fit anymore lol but the memories are forever. 🙌🏽

It’s seriously this simple. I get wanting the “perfect” content but don’t overthink it or make it harder than what it is. When I stopped feeling like I always had to be ready or have the best scenery & aesthetic it was a complete game changer.

I don’t batch my content or stress about what I’m going to post. I simply just put my phone up and record some videos of me doing everyday life & BAM throw a quick 4-5 second reel together. 🙌🏽

Biggest advice… HAVE FUN WITH IT! 

- Your Growth Guru 🌱

I feel like there’s this pressure put on us to know exactly what it is we want to do.. or that there are so many opportunities out there that I’m missing out if I don’t jump on one.. 

but it started to get so hard for me to show up excited because I didn’t feel aligned or have the passion I use to. 

I almost feel guilty for not knowing what I want to do or somewhat of a failure because I have tried all these things and I’m still searching for something that sets my soul on fire 

but I’m trusting the process and I know there’s something out there for me that will help me serve my purpose. 

So if you’re reading this and you feel like you’re in the same place of trying to discover what it is you want to do just know you aren’t alone 🤝🏽

I really struggled with drinking. It was my way to feel free, to feel seen, to feel like I had friends. There were so many days I woke up the next day feeling like shit, not physically but emotionally because I knew it was a temporary fix that was not helping me and it was just a vicious cycle. 

Fast forward to now.. I’m so grateful for this new chapter of life and it’s everything I prayed for. 🤍

But listen.. starting to read the Bible has been such a special experience. If you’re like me and avoided reading for so long because you thought it was too hard to understand - I get it.. 

I personally decided to go with a study Bible because it made it so much easier to understand and started streaming church on Sundays because the Pastor breaks it down to where it makes sense.. and I’m just in awe. 

I’m not perfect. There’s times I go days without reading but I’m trying to be better. 

There’s no “right” way to read but honestly just opening your heart to the word and really receiving the message.
